WEBVTT



00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:04.128
Have you noticed how ungrateful people are today?

00:00:04.288 --> 00:00:08.096
It's hard to even hear a please or thank you in public.

00:00:08.672 --> 00:00:15.424
My mother of blessed memory really pounded into me the importance of being thankful.

00:00:15.104 --> 00:00:22.496
on christmas day when we would unravel our presents i would be so anxious to go and play with the new toys.

00:00:22.496 --> 00:00:32.000
No, she said, you're not going to touch any of the presents until you have written a thank you letter to each person who gave you the gift.

00:00:32.448 --> 00:00:36.672
Well, she really trained me in the right way to go.

00:00:36.736 --> 00:00:37.856
and,

00:00:37.856 --> 00:00:47.904
I think she'd be pretty disappointed today if she knew that occasionally I had to take advantage of sending out an email, thank you. That's just not proper.

00:00:48.096 --> 00:00:52.032
Thankfulness is an important concept in our world today.

00:00:52.512 --> 00:00:53.568
And

00:00:53.696 --> 00:00:59.872
It's a story that happens to me and happens to you and also happened to Jesus.

00:01:00.768 --> 00:01:06.432
Being in the ministry, there are occasions when we get requests for

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:16.448
financial help from people, individuals and sometimes charities. And usually these are quite desperate appeals. We've got to have the money right away or something terrible.

00:01:15.968 --> 00:01:17.984
terrible is going to happen.

00:01:18.144 --> 00:01:27.552
Well, after investigating a few of the needs, we have from time to time responded to them by sending a check or wiring money to a situation.

00:01:28.032 --> 00:01:29.376
And then

00:01:29.408 --> 00:01:30.880
Silence!

00:01:31.616 --> 00:01:33.984
We never hear back from these people.

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:35.648
Did they receive the money?

00:01:35.808 --> 00:01:42.816
Well, you can contact them after a few days. Did you get the check in the post? Did you receive the wire transfer?

00:01:42.912 --> 00:01:44.640
Oh yeah, thanks a lot.

00:01:44.864 --> 00:01:47.456
That's all. We never hear from them again.

00:01:48.224 --> 00:01:53.248
There's even been an occasion recently where a family contacted me and,

00:01:53.024 --> 00:01:56.192
they said that they were going to be put out on the streets.

00:01:56.096 --> 00:01:58.208
If they didn't receive

00:01:57.888 --> 00:02:05.024
the money to pay the landlord right away. It was an urgent situation. Could I please help?

00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:15.840
Well, it happened to be raining and this had to be done right away, so I had to organize something with the bank. I had to go and address a letter with a first-class stamp.

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:24.480
stamp on it, go out in the rain and post that letter and rush the help that this family urgently needed, or they were going to be in terrible trouble.

00:02:24.256 --> 00:02:26.208
Terrible situation.

00:02:26.624 --> 00:02:27.712
Ha ha ha.

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:29.344
Nothing heard.

00:02:29.184 --> 00:02:32.384
For several days. so I finally called up and said,

00:02:32.352 --> 00:02:36.448
Hey, did you receive the check? Are you okay? Is everything?

00:02:36.224 --> 00:02:37.472
Happy now.

00:02:37.632 --> 00:02:40.096
Oh yeah, we received the check.

00:02:40.288 --> 00:02:44.416
By the way, would you be able to help us with next month's rent as well?

00:02:44.768 --> 00:02:46.240
Wow

00:02:46.944 --> 00:02:48.096
No, no.

00:02:48.256 --> 00:02:50.240
Expectation that

00:02:50.240 --> 00:02:56.640
there should be a thank you for that. I'm not really expecting the thank you, but it's just the acknowledgement of the gift.

00:02:57.280 --> 00:02:58.816
That's important.

00:02:59.104 --> 00:03:01.664
It happened to Jesus, as I said, when...

00:03:01.536 --> 00:03:10.976
there was the occasion when there were ten lepers and they were all in need of healing they had this debilitating terrible lifelong sickness.

00:03:10.656 --> 00:03:12.000
Jesus

00:03:11.808 --> 00:03:14.048
Healed all ten of them.

00:03:14.144 --> 00:03:19.904
And then, according to the Levitical law, they went off to be inspected by the

00:03:19.648 --> 00:03:25.632
the temple authorities, the rabbis, and to ritually cleanse themselves.

00:03:25.664 --> 00:03:27.008
And then Jesus came.

00:03:27.104 --> 00:03:28.896
Looked around and he said,

00:03:29.408 --> 00:03:31.680
Where are these ten that I healed?

00:03:31.808 --> 00:03:33.280
Only one

00:03:33.056 --> 00:03:34.912
Leper out of the ten.

00:03:34.848 --> 00:03:36.288
Came back and.

00:03:36.224 --> 00:03:41.056
acknowledged and said, "Thank you, Jesus, for what you've done for me."

00:03:42.208 --> 00:03:50.848
Well, it's an occasion for thankfulness because in the United States at this time of the year, in November, they celebrate Thanksgiving.

00:03:50.624 --> 00:03:54.464
Canada also celebrates in the month of October.

00:03:54.304 --> 00:03:57.664
Actually setting aside one day in the whole year

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:01.024
When you have a national holiday and you say

00:04:01.024 --> 00:04:02.176
Thank you.

00:04:02.048 --> 00:04:06.112
But who do you say thank you to and thank you for what?

00:04:06.752 --> 00:04:09.056
I found an interesting,

00:04:09.184 --> 00:04:13.856
idea from the Apostle Paul when he was writing to the

00:04:13.664 --> 00:04:15.616
the Christians in Rome.

